Phenol-Chloroform DNA Extraction

Duration
≃ 4h 

Materials and equipments
2 ml tubes 
1,5 ml tubes
ice
P1000 P200
centrifuge
microcentrifuge
vortex
shaking incubator (37 °C)
hot bath (65 °C) 
chemical hood

Solutions
Extraction Buffer (50mM Tris-HCL pH 8.0, 20 mM EDTA pH 8.0, 100 mM NaCl)
SDS 10% 
Lysozime 100 mg/ml
Phenol:Chloroform:IAA 25:24:1
Chloroform: IAA 24:1
Isopropanol 100% 
Sodium Acetate 3M pH 5.2 
EtOH 70% (COLD) 
Tris buffer (Tris-HCl 10 mM)

Procedure
Pellet resuspension: add 500 µL Extraction Buffer
Cellular breaking: add 20 µL Lysozyme 100 mg/mL 
Shaking incubator: 10’ at 37°C  
Vortex 30 sec
Add 100 µL SDS 10% - Incubation at T 65 °C x 30 min - up&down every 10 min
Add 1 Volume of Phenol : Chloroform : Isoamyl Alcohol (IAA) 25:24:1 and invert 100 times
Centrifuge 6 min x 7000 rpm 
Take the aqueous phase (transfer in a 2ml tube) and repeat two times IF the interface is dirty (or add 1 V Chloroform + IAA, 24:1) 
NB: discharge the phenolic phase in the appropriate tank in the 1D25 LAB 
Add 3 V of EtOH 100% + 0.1 volumes of Na-Acetate (3M pH 5.2) OR add 0.7 volumes 2 propanol (called also isopropanol) + 0.1 volumes of Na-Acetate (3M pH 5.2) 
Precipitation for a few minutes on the bank OR for 2 hours at T -20 °C OR overnight at room temperature
Centrifuge 30 min x 14000 rpm at T 4 °C and remove the supernatant
NB: the surnatant has to be discharged in the apposite tank in the 1D25 LAB ( this is an organic discharge)
Add 0.5 mL EtOH 70% (cold)
Centrifuge 5 min x 14000 rpm and remove all the supernatant
Dry at 37 °C  (for about 30 minutes)
Resuspend with 50 µL of TRIS buffer 10mM pH 8.8 and transfer in a 1.5 ml tube 
Keep DNA at -20 °C

Quantity check:
Quantification at NanoDrop

Quality and quantity check:
Run the DNA on Agarose gel (1%)

